From: Craftorithm Bot <bot@craftorithm.dev>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 20:58:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add trigger system
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two-phase trigger system for Craftorithm:
- Prepare phase: conditions evaluated on PrepareItemCraftEvent/PrepareSmithingEvent/PrepareAnvilEvent
  → conditions fail: clear result slot, block preview
- Actual phase: conditions evaluated on CraftItemEvent/SmithItemEvent/InventoryClickEvent
  → conditions pass: execute actions

YAML format (one file, multiple triggers, ID = filename:triggerId):
  type: 'crafting' | 'smithing' | 'anvil'
  recipes: [recipe keys]
  conditions: [script conditions, positive logic]
  actions: [script actions]
  priority/cooldown/enabled/per-player

Extensible: implement TriggerType interface + register to add new event types.

Files:
- TriggerType.java: interface for trigger types
- BuiltInTriggerTypes.java: crafting/smithing/anvil implementations
- Trigger.java: data model with condition evaluation + action execution
- TriggerContext.java: wraps Bukkit event, injects variables into ScriptContext
- TriggerCooldown.java: per-player/global cooldown management
- TriggerManager.java: lifecycle-managed loader, type registry, firePrepare/fire
- CraftTriggerListener.java: PrepareItemCraftEvent + CraftItemEvent
- SmithingTriggerListener.java: PrepareSmithingEvent + SmithItemEvent
- AnvilTriggerListener.java: PrepareAnvilEvent + InventoryClickEvent
